                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d806">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867.24/295</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Acting Secretary of
                        State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-04-08">April 8,
                            1942</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Ambassador called to see me this morning. The Ambassador stated that
                    he had just received a cable from his Foreign Office stating that the British
                    Government agreed to the proposals of <pb facs="0704" n="692" xml:id="pg_692"/>
                    this Government concerning the manner of determining the Lease-Lend material to
                    be furnished Turkey.</p>
                <p>I said that I was very glad to receive this information and that I trusted that
                    his Embassy would immediately discuss these questions with Mr. Acheson.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>S[<hi rend="smallcaps">umner</hi>] W[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >elles</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
